item.title: N bombs within, warning. White person calls black ICE agent a "house Nword working for the KKK"
item.description:
Hadn't seen this on imgur yet. Black commentary, cultural permissiveness, and potentially offensive language and attitudes within. Lezzgo
Case study in question
A fantastic discourse on the perennial question of "can white people use the N word." This conversation may be disconcerting to some. To many people of color, it is a regular occurrence to know that wypipo (white people) still frequently use Nbombs at POC, permission or not.
This is NOT an exception or loophole to the socially accepted norms that white people are rightfully scrutinized and sanctioned for dropping Nbombs. It may be an override given very specific circumstances.
There is a sentiment in skinfolk (POC) communities that black conservatives aren't maga, they're just desperate for white acceptance. They listen to white people opinion more than black. So, maybe this WAS the right messenger after all. This isn't afternoon high tea, there will offenses given, and taken, in the commentary discourse. Go forth with curiosity, courtesy, and comedy. Can wypipo use the N word? Can THIS white person use the term "house Nword" for black ICE officers? These are the philosophical queries of our time
